and 50 percent of their time
here in Texas.

02:01.033 --> 02:02.774
So we're trying to get Noah
to move to Texas.

02:02.818 --> 02:04.298
I mean, if you're gonna be
true Texan,

02:04.341 --> 02:05.603
your boot game
has to be strong.

02:05.647 --> 02:07.170
<i>- Yeah, and Rod Patrick
is like--</i>

02:07.214 --> 02:08.171
how would you describe it?

02:08.215 --> 02:09.303
It's like the Mercedes
of boots.

02:09.346 --> 02:10.217
- It's like
the Ferrari of boots.

02:10.260 --> 02:12.262
- For--yeah.

02:12.306 --> 02:14.395
- Oh, hey guys.
- Hello, hello.

02:14.438 --> 02:16.440
- Bobby, this is
my brother-in-law, Noah.

02:16.484 --> 02:17.528
- Noah, it's a pleasure.

02:17.572 --> 02:19.182
- And my sister-in-law, Lacey.

02:19.226 --> 02:20.314
- Lacey.
- Lacey, Bobby Smith.

02:20.357 --> 02:21.532
- Okay, you ready?

02:21.576 --> 02:22.707
Can you fix it?
- Whoa!

02:22.751 --> 02:24.970
- Oh, Noah, no!

02:25.014 --> 02:26.929
- Oh, bless his heart.

02:26.972 --> 02:28.365
- Okay.

02:28.409 --> 02:29.975
- I think you've set the bar
pretty low.

02:30.019 --> 02:31.455
- Hey!

02:31.499 --> 02:34.110
You have nowhere but up now.
- Nowhere--ha ha ha ha!

02:34.154 --> 02:36.808
- Oh, my, all right,
I see how this is gonna go.

02:36.852 --> 02:38.245
So is this like
a normal thing when you go

02:38.288 --> 02:39.420
boot shopping
that they just harass you

02:39.463 --> 02:40.812
