02:56.306 --> 02:58.090
that I need to--

02:59.179 --> 03:00.267
- Show me the walk.

03:00.310 --> 03:01.616
Is it, like, a heel-to-toe?

03:01.659 --> 03:03.313
- It's just sort
of a "You don't know me,

03:03.357 --> 03:04.271
but you wanna know me."

03:04.314 --> 03:05.446
- Oh!

03:05.489 --> 03:06.838
- You know? Very confident.

03:06.882 --> 03:08.492
- I think there's
a little wiggle in there.

03:08.536 --> 03:10.233
- Jeff, we want to get
to a plan B here.

03:10.277 --> 03:11.278
- Yep, plan B.

03:11.321 --> 03:12.453
We're gonna narrow you up.

03:12.496 --> 03:13.976
So let's slip this on.

03:14.019 --> 03:15.238
- Where would I wear these?

03:15.282 --> 03:16.544
- Anywhere you couldn't wear
those, don't go.

03:16.587 --> 03:19.024
- Hey, that's a good point.
- I like that!

03:19.068 --> 03:20.112
- That's a really good point.

03:20.156 --> 03:21.853
- Can you give me a "Yeehaw"?

03:21.897 --> 03:23.290
- No, no.
- No.

03:23.333 --> 03:24.552
- Too far.
- You could do, like, a...

03:26.249 --> 03:27.642
- That looks like a dance.

03:27.685 --> 03:29.121
- You're new boot goofin'.

03:29.165 --> 03:30.862
<i>♪</i>

03:30.906 --> 03:32.124
- You look super cool.

03:32.168 --> 03:34.866
- What is happening right now?

03:34.910 --> 03:35.867
- It's the two-step.

03:37.129 --> 03:38.957
- Ooh, those are really
good-looking too.

03:39.001 --> 03:41.351
- Really excited he's embracing
Texas things.

03:41.395 --> 03:42.352
- I'm excited for him.

03:42.396 --> 03:43.571
- Oh, how much are those?

03:43.614 --> 03:45.486
- That's a good question.
- About $3,000.

03:45.529 --> 03:48.271
- Take 'em off, take 'em off,
take 'em off!

03:48.315 --> 03:50.447
I'll spend some money
on some things.

03:50.491 --> 03:52.362
But cowboy boots?

03:52.406 --> 03:53.755
Erin, is this normal?

03:53.798 --> 03:55.365
- You have to have
the top-of-the-line boots.

03:55.409 --> 03:57.106
- 3,000.
- Or you will get made fun of.

03:57.149 --> 03:58.238
- It's like the guys' version

03:58.281 --> 03:59.848
of, like, a nice bag or a shoe.

03:59.891 --> 04:01.806
And if it gets him to move
to Texas

04:01.850 --> 04:03.286
it's so worth it.

04:03.330 --> 04:05.070
- Yeah, we'll just take
that out of the house fund.

04:05.114 --> 04:07.769
Smaller house, bigger boots.
I don't know, it's Texas.

04:07.812 --> 04:09.336
- Oh! That should be
on a t-shirt.

04:09.379 --> 04:10.772
"Small house, bigger boots."

04:10.815 --> 04:13.165
- Hey, you know what they say
about bigger boots.

04:13.209 --> 04:14.732
I mean, Scott's a size 14.

04:16.778 --> 04:18.040
- These are my favorite.
- You like those?

04:18.083 --> 04:19.302
- They're a little bit above
my budget though.

04:19.346 --> 04:20.347
I think I have $1,000 limit.

04:20.390 --> 04:22.914
- No, we'll do those.

04:22.958 --> 04:25.308
- Oh, stop it.
- Those are so cool.

04:25.352 --> 04:26.918
- You have
a great brother-in-law.

04:26.962 --> 04:28.746
- Hey, I'm trying to get him
to Texas.

04:28.790 --> 04:30.618
- It's hard for me
to wrap my head around

04:30.661 --> 04:33.142
walking through a pile
of cow poop in $3,000 boots.

04:33.185 --> 04:34.578
- You're a real Texan now.

04:34.622 --> 04:35.971
- Thank you.
- Yay!

04:36.014 --> 04:36.972
Yay.
- We did it.

04:37.015 --> 04:38.016
- We got some boots!

04:38.060 --> 04:39.279
<i>- Whoo.
- Yeehaw!</i>

04:42.369 --> 04:44.284
- Zurie,
she and I were writing music

04:44.327 --> 04:45.937
this morning at the ranch.

04:45.981 --> 04:47.852
- Okay.
- Go!

04:47.896 --> 04:49.376
- ♪ Here's what I want,
what you want? ♪

04:49.419 --> 04:51.900
♪ I want some fries,
I want some sauce on the side ♪

04:51.943 --> 04:53.728
♪ You better remember
the chicken I order ♪

