♪ Or you'll get knocked
in the head with a quarter ♪

04:55.512 --> 04:57.209
- Good.
- ♪ I'm about to eat a pickle

04:57.253 --> 04:58.385
♪ I bet you a nickel

04:58.428 --> 04:59.951
♪ That my tummy will get
a little tickle ♪

04:59.995 --> 05:00.952
- Oh, that's good.

05:00.996 --> 05:01.997
You're like a poet,

05:02.040 --> 05:03.390
and you didn't know it.

05:03.433 --> 05:09.091
<i>♪</i>

05:14.314 --> 05:16.838
- Why do they want to lick you
right in the mouth?

05:28.197 --> 05:29.198
- Hey!

05:29.241 --> 05:30.504
- Why are you honking?

05:30.547 --> 05:33.071
- I just got my mixes back
for my record.

05:33.115 --> 05:35.335
And I'm so--I want you
to hear it with me.

05:35.378 --> 05:37.989
- I don't understand why did
we have to listen to music

05:38.033 --> 05:40.383
in your car?
- You can't beat the sound...

05:40.427 --> 05:41.863
in a car.
- Makes sense.

05:41.906 --> 05:42.907
- A closed space.

05:42.951 --> 05:44.213
People don't just go
to a studio

05:44.256 --> 05:45.475
and listen to a song.

05:45.519 --> 05:47.434
Usually it's always
in your car.

05:47.477 --> 05:49.740
Gotta hear this.

05:49.784 --> 05:50.785
Okay.

05:50.828 --> 05:52.830
This is called "Wild Horse."

05:52.874 --> 05:54.615
- "Wild horse."
- I wrote this by myself

05:54.658 --> 05:55.833
at the, um, piano.

05:57.444 --> 05:59.837
<i>♪ It's history in the making</i>

05:59.881 --> 06:02.274
<i>♪ What we're living</i>

06:02.318 --> 06:05.365
<i>♪ It'll tear you up</i>

06:05.408 --> 06:06.757
- You wrote this?

06:06.801 --> 06:10.152
- By myself. <i>
♪ Gonna rip your heart out</i>

06:10.195 --> 06:11.719
<i>♪ Some days</i>

06:11.762 --> 06:14.678
<i>Music is how I best express
myself.</i>

06:14.722 --> 06:16.288
We're a big music family.

06:16.332 --> 06:19.379
- It was the way my family was
and it's passed on to me.

06:19.422 --> 06:20.510
You're so good at it.

06:20.554 --> 06:22.207
It's such a God-given gift.

06:22.251 --> 06:24.122
- Strings.

06:24.166 --> 06:27.691
<i>♪ And the world's
spinning around ♪</i>

06:27.735 --> 06:29.737
<i>♪ With a dancing sunrise</i>

06:29.780 --> 06:32.304
- You don't mind if I take
some credit here, do you?

06:32.348 --> 06:33.654
- Okay.
- I mean, who pushed you

06:33.697 --> 06:35.395
to sing at NASCAR?

06:35.438 --> 06:37.092
- You did, okay.
- Thank you.

06:37.135 --> 06:40.922
