"God Bless America."

06:40.965 --> 06:41.966
You can do it.

06:42.010 --> 06:45.970
<i>♪</i>

06:46.014 --> 06:47.537
- That was so scary!

06:47.581 --> 06:48.582
- You did great.

06:48.625 --> 06:49.670
- Oh, thanks, Dad.

06:49.713 --> 06:51.193
I'm so glad I just did that.

06:51.236 --> 06:54.239
<i>♪ I'll do the things
that you do ♪</i>

06:54.283 --> 06:56.807
<i>♪ When we're listening
to Coldplay ♪</i>

06:56.851 --> 06:59.244
<i>♪ On a Sunday in the rain</i>

06:59.288 --> 07:01.246
<i>♪</i>

07:01.290 --> 07:04.119
<i>♪ Mm</i>

07:04.162 --> 07:06.774
- You got a sultry way
of singing.

07:06.817 --> 07:08.863
<i>- Yeah, I feel like
I really bared my soul</i>

07:08.906 --> 07:10.995
<i>when I was recording this.</i>

07:11.039 --> 07:12.736
- So, lemme ask you now.

07:12.780 --> 07:14.956
You're on Spot--what do you
call it?

07:14.999 --> 07:17.480
- Spotify.
- Get on Spotify.

07:17.524 --> 07:20.178
So, I mean, do you tour now?

07:20.222 --> 07:21.615
Do you what? What happens?

07:21.658 --> 07:23.007
- If people like it,

07:23.051 --> 07:25.183
then it'll get
on popular "playlists."

07:25.227 --> 07:27.621
And if it gets
on a popular playlist,

07:27.664 --> 07:29.666
I mean, you could get
a million streams.

07:29.710 --> 07:31.146
- That a million dollars?

07:31.189 --> 07:32.495
- No, I wish it were.

07:32.539 --> 07:34.410
- CDs are pretty much history?

07:34.454 --> 07:36.281
- People don't have CDs
anymore.

07:36.325 --> 07:37.587
- Wow.

07:37.631 --> 07:41.112
Yeah, I remember when I started
in the '70s.

07:41.156 --> 07:44.768
My first album I shot the cover
for the album.

07:44.812 --> 07:46.944
<i>In the bottom of it
an old train station</i>

07:46.988 --> 07:50.252
<i>in Nashville, so the
photography and words</i>

07:50.295 --> 07:52.733
to describe the album
were on the cover.

07:52.776 --> 07:54.082
- Yeah.
- See, I did

07:54.125 --> 07:56.954
50-something thousand copies
of my first album.

07:56.998 --> 07:59.087
And then I got dropped
from the label

07:59.130 --> 08:01.524
'cause that's not--that wasn't
enough.

08:01.568 --> 08:03.483
You think I should do
a country album?

08:03.526 --> 08:04.832
- No.
- No.

08:04.875 --> 08:06.442
Who's gonna buy a Terry
Bradshaw country album?

08:06.486 --> 08:07.574
- People don't buy albums
anymore.

08:07.617 --> 08:09.532
- Oh, well, who's
gonna download my songs?

08:09.576 --> 08:11.534
I've got an idea

08:11.578 --> 08:15.364
that I think is really gonna
benefit you.

08:15.407 --> 08:16.670
- Okay, Dad.

08:16.713 --> 08:19.281
- We gotta go on "Spotalip"
and get--

08:19.324 --> 08:20.891
- Spotify!
- Spotify.

08:20.935 --> 08:23.981
<i>What if I, hippa pie,
lippa pie.</i>

08:30.814 --> 08:33.513
<i>♪</i>

08:37.081 --> 08:39.823
<i>- Leland,
this looks perfect.</i>

08:39.867 --> 08:43.218
She's gonna love it.
Yeah, 5,000's just the start.

08:43.261 --> 08:45.133
Tammy!

08:47.309 --> 08:48.528
Tammy!

08:48.571 --> 08:50.573
<i>♪</i>

08:50.617 --> 08:51.922
<i>Tammy!</i>

08:53.533 --> 08:56.927
Hang on.

08:57.885 --> 08:59.887
- What?
- Ta--oh, hey.

08:59.930 --> 09:02.019
- Why do you always yell
for me?

09:02.063 --> 09:07.329
What would happen if you got
up and came to where I was?

09:07.372 --> 09:08.591
- I guess I'm lazy.

09:08.635 --> 09:10.593
I just...
you've spoiled me rotten,

09:10.637 --> 09:11.725
so what do you expect?

09:11.768 --> 09:13.117
- It makes me feel needed.

09:13.161 --> 09:14.249
- You are needed.

09:14.292 --> 09:16.207
- Okay.

09:16.251 --> 09:17.426
- Yeah, okay.

09:17.469 --> 09:19.297
I'll call you back.
We're good, no, no.

09:19.341 --> 09:20.603
Go with it.
If there's any changes,

09:20.647 --> 09:21.604
I'll call you today.

09:21.648 --> 09:22.605
- Who're you talking to?

09:22.649 --> 09:23.780
- The guy in Nashville

09:23.824 --> 09:26.261
that I'm having
the album covers printed

09:26.304 --> 09:27.262
for Rachel.

09:27.305 --> 09:28.611
- You're making
the album cover?

09:28.655 --> 09:30.047
- Yeah.
- Well, don't you think

09:30.091 --> 09:32.223
she might want to have
an opinion on this?

09:33.529 --> 09:36.837
- People don't buy albums
anymore.

09:36.880 --> 09:39.753
- All right, Leland,
call you today.

09:39.796 --> 09:40.841
- She knows you're making
the cover?

09:40.884 --> 09:42.799
- No, not yet.

09:42.843 --> 09:48.239
- Does that bring any other
scenario to mind for you?

09:50.067 --> 09:53.114
- "Seal the Deal
with Rachel Bradshaw."

09:53.157 --> 09:55.464
We got 'em on all the benches
all over town.

09:55.507 --> 09:56.465
They're everywhere.

09:56.508 --> 09:57.640
- You already put 'em up--out?

09:57.684 --> 09:59.642
- Yeah, yeah, I did it for you.

09:59.686 --> 10:03.124
- I don't think he understands
what the phrase "Seal the deal"

10:03.167 --> 10:03.951
really means.

10:03.994 --> 10:05.474
- Every man in Dallas

10:05.517 --> 10:07.911
will see that
and wanna call her for a date.

10:10.784 --> 10:12.002
- That didn't go real good.

10:12.046 --> 10:14.222
- Asking for input
is a good idea.

10:14.265 --> 10:16.311
- I--well--

10:16.354 --> 10:19.227
- She's a young woman
working on a career.

10:19.270 --> 10:22.622
She wants to put her ideas
into it.

10:22.665 --> 10:25.102
You're kinda taking that away
from her, don't you think?

10:25.146 --> 10:28.149
- There's a very thin line

10:28.192 --> 10:31.282
between interfering
and helping.

10:31.326 --> 10:33.458
- Yes, it's called
a phone line.

10:36.723 --> 10:38.681
I'm gonna call Rachel.

10:38.725 --> 10:39.682
- Good luck.

10:41.728 --> 10:44.034
<i>- Hi!
- Guess what I'm doing.</i>

10:44.078 --> 10:44.861
<i>- What?</i>

10:44.905 --> 10:46.558
- Get this, you ready?

10:46.602 --> 10:47.516
<i>- Yes.
- I'm helping you</i>

10:47.559 --> 10:48.735
with your music career.

10:48.778 --> 10:51.868
I'm designing an album cover
for you.

10:51.912 --> 10:54.479
Can't wait to show it to you.

10:54.523 --> 10:56.394
- Hey, before you thank me--

10:56.438 --> 10:58.092
- It's all at my expense.

10:58.135 --> 11:00.747
I'm paying for the whole thing.

11:00.790 --> 11:01.704
- Thank you.

